:h1 res=1000.General

:p.Welcome to VRAID, the first (to my knowledge) shareware RAID
solution for &OS2..  Instead of buying an expensive RAID controller you
d47 10
d58 1
a58 1
:p.This software :link refid=features reftype=fn.features:elink.&colon.
d60 4
a63 12
:ul.
:li.Single (an array containing a single disk or array)
:li.Chaining (two or more disks or arrays combined by adding one behind the other)
:li.Striping (RAID 0)
:li.Mirroring (RAID 1)
:li.You can combine any combination of RAID levels to create the array
&OS2. should use for file storage.  There is no :link refid=limits
reftype=fn.limit:elink. on how complicated your array structure
becomes.
:li.:link refid=Build reftype=fn.Build:elink. and :link refid=Rebuild
reftype=fn.Rebuild:elink. Processes are done in the background.
:eul.
d65 4
a69 1
:p.How is it done?
d71 2
a72 5
:p.Well, &FLT. is a small filter driver which intercepts
OS2DASD.DMD operation and combines non-removable disks of any kind to
RAID arrays.  This process is transparent to anything installed after
&FLT..  For FAT, hpfs.ifs, ext2fs.ifs and any other software you use a
RAID array looks just as an ordinary disk.
d74 6
a79 1
:p.This means you have to do the following steps:
