:p.This chapter describes &EXE., a program to define RAID drives
d303 2
a304 2
:p.As it is difficult to discuss the whole matter (drives made out of
drives which are known by &OS2. as drives) I deciced to put up a
d307 26
a332 2
:ul.
:li.&OS2. devices / &OS2. drives
a333 17
:p.Those spinning things as you have known them ever.  Every device
contains one or more partitions and every partition may contain a
filesystem supported by &OS2..  A supported filesystem (FAT, HPFS,
EXT2FS, ...) is assigned a drive letter.

:li.&PDEV.

:p.Whenever a &OS2. device contains a VRAID partition (partition type 0x7C
if you wonder) that partition is called a &PDEV..  &PDEV.s may
become part of...

:li.&ARRAY. (Single, Striping, Chaining, Mirror, ...)

:p.&ARRAY.s are build from &PDEV.s and may be part of other
&ARRAY.s, building a freely definable disk structure.  The topmost
&ARRAY. is reported by &FLT. to &OS2. and accessible by FDISK as a
whole.
a334 1
:eul.
