:p.Devices known to &OS2. :hp1.and:ehp1. inuse by &OS2. (there is at
least one partition and an &OS2.-supported filesystem resides in it).
You can't build a &ARRAY. from this type of icon.

:p.Whenever &EXE. hits such a device during it's drive scan, the
following message box will appear:

:cgraphic.
      
       Can't lock physical disk N, ignore this 
       error and allow writing?                
                                               
                                     
       Yes   No                            
                                     
      
:ecgraphic.

Where N is a zerobased index over all &OS2. accessable disks.  Usually
this means the situation described above (disk contains FAT, HPTS,
EXT2 or NTFS partition) and that &EXE. shouldn't write to this device.
But as &OS2. isn't errorfree this message does sometimes appear on
disks which don't have an &OS2. partition and therefore you are asked
what you do think about disk N.  Answer "Yes" if disk N is free to be
used by VRAID, answer "No" if it contains an &OS2. related partition
and no free additional room.

:p.If you answer "No" the disk will get a 3D look white box.  If you
answer "Yes" the disk will get a 3D look grey box.
