a583 1
:dt.Drag and Drop
a584 2
:dd.It is possible to drag an &ARRAY. or &PDEV. onto a RAID 1,
4 or 5 array.  The dragged device will become part of the array.
a585 6
:p.Becoming part of an array means that the dropped device gets data
from the array and will be overwritten.  This overwriting is either a
build (RAID 1) or rebuild (RAID 4 and 5 in :hp2.fail:ehp2. state)
starting on next reboot or the device is added as a spare (RAID 4 and
5) and will get overwritten by a rebuild on next switch to
:hp2.fail:ehp2. state.
