:li.&FLT. will hide drives with a VRAID partition from OS/2 and will
instead report your defined arrays to OS/2.
a89 18
:p.As this is work in process only some RAID levels are
implemented. However, it's intention is to supply all major RAID
levels to the average OS/2 user.

:p.Currently implemented:
:ul compact.
:li.Single (an array containing a single disk or array)
:li.Chaining (two or more disks or arrays combined by adding one behind the other)
:li.Striping (RAID 0)
:li.Mirroring (RAID 1)
:eul.

:p.You can combine any combination of RAID levels to create the array
OS/2 should use for file storage.  There is no limit on how
complicated your array structure becomes (well, there is a memory
limitation in &FLT. but I don't expect you to reach this).


